name: Philly Cheesesteak Smothered Tater Tots
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(2 pound)-package', 'name': 'tater tots'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'red bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) box', 'name': 'frozen sandwich beef'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Montreal steak seasoning'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded mozzarella cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Line a large baking sheet with foil; arrange tater tots on the sheet in a single layer.. Bake in the preheated oven until golden, about 20 minutes.. Meanwhile, cook and stir onion, green pepper, and red  pepper in a large skillet over medium-high heat for 5 minutes. Add beef, Worcestershire sauce, and steak seasoning. Cook until most of liquid has evaporated, about 6 minutes.. Divide beef mixture over baked tater tots with a slotted spoon. Sprinkle shredded cheese over the top.. Bake until cheese is melted and beginning to brown, about 5 minutes more.

name: Caper Pesto
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups packed fresh', 'name': 'basil leaves'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pine nuts'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green onions'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh dill'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'capers'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'lemon zest'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'smashed garlic'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}
steps: Gather the ingredients.. Process basil, Parmesan, oil, pine nuts, green onions, dill, capers, juice, zest, garlic, salt, and pepper in a food processor until nearly smooth.. Chill in an airtight container up to 1 week; freeze up to 3 months.

name: Date and Dried Cherry Mostarda
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'medjool dates'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'tart cherries, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'shallot'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white wine'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'white balsamic vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'orange zest'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'orange juice'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crystallized ginger'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground mustard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'mustard powder'}
steps: Combine dates, cherries, shallot, wine, vinegar, orange zest, orange juice, sugar, crystallized ginger, salt, cinnamon, and crushed red pepper in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, until liquid is absorbed and fruit is softened, about 10 minutes.. Stir in butter, mustard, and mustard powder. Simmer, uncovered, until mixture is thickened and jam-like, 2 to 3 minutes. Serve warm or at room temperature.

name: Loaded Broccoli Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'broccoli florets'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon, coarsely chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10-ounce) can', 'name': 'condensed cream of chicken soup'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '30', 'unit': None, 'name': 'crackers, coarsely crushed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, melted'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly coat a 2-quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.. Cook broccoli in a large pot of boiling, lightly salted water for 1 minute; drain. Rinse with cold water; drain again and set aside.. Cook bacon in a large skillet over medium until crisp. Using a slotted spoon, remove bacon to a paper towel lined plate. Crumble bacon when cool.. Add onion to the skillet with bacon drippings; cook over medium about 5 minutes or until tender.. Meanwhile, combine soup , sour cream, garlic powder, salt, and pepper in a large bowl.. Add broccoli, bacon, and cooked onions to the soup mixture and stir to combine. Add cheese, stir.. Transfer broccoli mixture to prepared baking dish.. Combine crushed crackers and melted butter in a small bowl. Sprinkle crumb mixture over casserole.. Bake 45 minutes or until bubbly and golden.. Serve hot and enjoy!

name: Cheesy Mashed Sweet Potatoes
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 3/4', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'sweet potatoes, peeled and cut into 2-inch chunks'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'sage leaves'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'half and half'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecan halves'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': '1 tablespoon chopped sage leaves, plus more for garnish'}
steps: Put sweet potatoes and sage leaves in a 2-quart baking dish; top with 1/2 cup water. Microwave, covered, on High, stirring halfway through, until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes. Discard sage. Add Parmesan, half-and-half, salt, and pepper. Mash with a potato masher until smooth.. Heat oil in a small skillet over medium heat. Toast pecans, panko, and chopped sage, stirring frequently, about 3 minutes. Sprinkle mixture over sweet potato mixture. Garnish with additional sage leaves.

name: Roasted Red Pepper Sauce
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'red bell peppers'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lemon, juiced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'cloves garlic'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'ounce', 'name': 'fresh basil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'prepared horseradish'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}
steps: Preheat a grill for medium heat and lightly oil the grate. Cut peppers in half. Remove and discard stems, seeds, and membranes.. Place peppers, skin side up, on the preheated grill, directly over heat; cook until slightly charred, 3 to 5 minutes. Turn peppers over and char the other side. Remove from the grill to cool slightly.. Combine peppers, mayonnaise, lemon juice, garlic, horseradish, and smoked paprika in the container of a blender; cover and blend until smooth.

name: Italian-Style Green Bean and Artichoke Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(9 ounce) packages', 'name': 'frozen artichoke hearts'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '(28 ounce) cans', 'name': 'green beans'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'chopped parsley for garnish'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Lightly grease a 9x13-inch baking dish.. Combine Italian bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, garlic, salt, and pepper  in a large bowl. Reserve 1/3 cup breadcrumb mixture and set aside.. Add artichokes, green beans, and 1/2 cup olive oil to the bowl and gently fold to combine well. Pour mixture into the prepared baking dish and sprinkle with reserved breadcrumb mixture. Drizzle with remaining olive oil; cover with foil.. Bake in the preheated oven until heated through, about 30 minutes. Uncover and bake until lightly golden and bubbly around the edges, 10 to 15 minutes more. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

name: Baked Polenta Marinara
ingredients: {'quantity': '3 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'polenta'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup shredded', 'name': 'mozzarella, divided'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'marinara sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'prosciutto, shredded'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Lightly oil a 9x13-inch baking dish; set aside.. Bring chicken broth to a boil in a saucepan, and whisk in polenta and salt. Immediately reduce temperature to medium, and cook polenta, stirring continuously, until most of the liquid is absorbed and polenta is thick, about 15 minutes. Remove from heat.. Stir Parmesan cheese, 1/4 cup mozzarella, and butter into polenta. Pour mixture into the prepared baking dish and smooth the top.. Bake in the preheated oven until polenta is fairly firm, about 40 minutes. It will firm a bit more on standing.. Remove polenta from the oven; let stand for 5 minutes. Spread marinara over the top, then sprinkle evenly with remaining 1/2 cup mozzarella. Sprinkle top with shredded prosciutto.. Bake polenta until cheese is bubbling and golden brown, about 15 minutes more. Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

name: Air Fryer Baked Yams
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'yam'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Scrub yam clean and dry with a paper towel. Rub all over with olive oil.. Place yam in the preheated air fryer, and cook until tender when pierced with a fork, 15 to 20 minutes.

name: Peanut Butter Sauce
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sweetened condensed milk'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Heat peanut butter and sweetened condensed milk in a saucepan over medium-low heat, stirring until well incorporated and smooth. Stir in milk.. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and salt.

name: Spicy Creamy Cucumber Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'English', 'name': 'cucumbers'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'plain Greek yogurt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh lime juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chili sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ketchup'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'hot sauce (such as Tabasco'}
steps: Place sliced cucumbers into a large bowl.. Whisk Greek yogurt, lime juice, Thai chili sauce, ketchup, and hot sauce together in a small bowl until smooth; stir into sliced cucumbers. Refrigerate for 30 minutes before serving.

name: Mississippi Mud Potatoes
ingredients: {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'diced potatoes'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic cloves'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green onions'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Spray an 8x8-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Set aside.. Combine potatoes, cheese, bacon, onion, mayonnaise, garlic, salt, and pepper in a large bowl. Transfer to the prepared dish.. Bake until potatoes are fork tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Top with green onions.

name: Cheesy Zucchini Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'low-sodium chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'long grain rice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded unpeeled zucchini'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cheese'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Bring broth to a boil in a saucepan; stir in rice. Cover, reduce heat to low, and cook until rice is tender and all liquid is absorbed, 20 to 25 minutes.. Remove from heat. Stir in melted butter. Add zucchini and cheese. Stir, cover and let sit until cheese is melted, about 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

name: Corn with Tarragon and Lime
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.4 ounce) package', 'name': 'corn'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter, cubed'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh tarragon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'lime, zested'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Empty frozen corn into a 2-quart saucepan, and stir in water. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, cover, and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 4 minutes. Drain well.. Return saucepan to the stove over low heat, add butter, tarragon, lime zest, and juice. Stir until butter has melted and corn is warm, about 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, and serve.

name: Mint Yogurt Sauce
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Greek yogurt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh mint'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'freshly squeezed lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic,'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper,'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}
steps: Combine yogurt, mint, lemon juice, garlic, salt, pepper and cumin in a bowl. Stir until well combined.

name: Parmesan Pesto Roasted Cauliflower
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'head', 'name': 'cauliflower'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pesto'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. In a large bowl, toss the cauliflower florets with olive oil, salt, and pepper until evenly coated. Spread cauliflower evenly in a single layer on the prepared baking sheet. Set the bowl aside.. Roast in the preheated oven until golden and crispy on the edges, 25 to 30 minutes, turning halfway through cooking time.. Transfer hot cauliflower back to the bowl and toss with pesto and Parmesan cheese. Serve immediately.

name: Southwestern Twice Baked Sweet Potatoes
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'sweet potatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'chipotle peppers in adobo'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'maple syrup'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green onion'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '2 3/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'pepper Jack cheese,'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with foil or parchment. Rub potatoes evenly with oil and sprinkle evenly with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt. Pierce potatoes with a fork and place them on the prepared sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven until completely tender, 35 to 40 minutes.. Meanwhile, place bacon in a large skillet and cook over medium-high heat, turning occasionally, until crisp, about 10 minutes. Reserve 1 tablespoon bacon grease. Drain bacon on paper towels, chop, and set aside.. Cut the top 1/4 off the top of each potato and scoop out most of the potato, reserving intact skins with flesh about 1/8-inch-thick.. Add scooped flesh to a bowl with butter, reserved bacon grease, and remaining salt, and mash until creamy and only small lumps remain. Stir in chipotles and adobo sauce, maple syrup, green onions, sour cream, and 1 cup cheese. Divide filling evenly among potatoes and top each with 1 tablespoon cheese. Return potatoes to the lined baking sheet.. Return to the oven and bake until hot and cheese is melted, about 15 minutes.

name: Phyllis’s Braised Collard Greens
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'smoked ham hocks'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'collard greens - cl'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': '1 teaspoon red pepper flakes, or'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Place smoked ham hocks in a large pot and add 4 cups of water. Cover and simmer over low heat until meat nearly pulls away from the bone, and the skin is a little tender, about 1 hour.. Remove ham hocks from the pot. Add collards and red pepper flakes, and season with salt and pepper. Cover and simmer until tender, about 1 hour. Add ham hocks back in and cook for another 15 minutes.

name: Basic Congee
ingredients: {'quantity': '7', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'stock'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'rice'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ginger'}
steps: Add stock, rice, salt, and ginger to a large saucepan, and bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally, making sure rice does not stick to the bottom. Reduce the heat to low; simmer for 1 hour.

name: Roscoe's Jollof Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'red bell pepper,'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic cloves'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh ginger'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'jalapeno'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'cotch bonnet pepper, cut in half'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'palm oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'red onions,'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'tomato paste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground turmeric'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'Maggi'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'jasmine rice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'thyme, dried or fresh'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'bay leaf'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}
steps: Combine tomatoes, red bell pepper, red onion, garlic, ginger, red jalapeno, and Scotch bonnet in a blender; blend until smooth.. Heat palm oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat. Add onions and cook, stirring frequently, until softened, 6 to 8 minutes. Remove onions from the pan.. Pour in tomato base and cook on low until reduced by half. Stir in tomato paste, turmeric, Maggi cubes, and smoked paprika. Cook, stirring, until the mixture reduces and becomes an even deeper red, about 2 minutes.. Stir in rice, thyme, and bay leaf, and season with salt and pepper. Stir in water and cover with a lid. Cook on low for 35 minutes. Turn off the heat and let sit covered for 15 minutes.. Fluff rice with a fork, taste and adjust seasonings, and serve.

name: Smashed Sambal Broccoli
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'broccoli, cut into florets'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Asian-style chili paste'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'maple syrup'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'toasted sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'toasted sesame seeds'}
steps: Set oven rack about 6 inches from heat source and preheat broiler. Put a steamer basket in a large saucepan. Add water to just below steamer basket. Bring to a boil. Add broccoli to steamer basket; reduce heat to medium-low. Steam, covered, until crisp-tender, 4 minutes.. When cool enough to handle, spread broccoli on a 10x15-inch rimmed baking sheet. Using the bottom of a sturdy glass, flatten broccoli florets to 1/2 inch thick. Drizzle with vegetable oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper; toss to coat.. Broil until charred around edges, 5 to 7 minutes.. Meanwhile, stir together chili paste, garlic, maple syrup, and sesame oil in a small bowl. Spoon over broccoli. Sprinkle with sesame seeds.

name: Sausage Green Bean Potato Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'chicken apple sausage'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onion,'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried thyme'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'low-sodium chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'half-and-half'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'fresh green beans'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'potatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'carrots'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'fried onions'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) and grease a 3-quart baking dish.. Brown sausage pieces in a nonstick skillet over medium heat, 3 to 5 minutes; remove from the pan to a large bowl.. In the same skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Add onions, and cook, stirring, until soft, about 3 minutes. Stir in garlic and cook another 30 seconds. Stir in thyme; season with salt and pepper.. Sprinkle flour over onions and garlic, and stir until flour has been absorbed, about 1 to 2 minutes. Stir in chicken broth and half-and-half. Bring to a boil, while stirring, then reduce to a simmer and cook, stirring, until sauce thickens and coats the back of a spoon, 3 to 5 minutes. Remove skillet from the heat.. Add green beans, potatoes, and carrots to the bowl with sausage; add sauce and stir to coat all ingredients with the sauce. Transfer mixture to the prepared baking dish. Cover with foil.. Bake in the preheated oven for 45 minutes. Remove foil, stir, and sprinkle fried onions on top.. Continue to bake until casserole is hot and bubbly and onions have crisped slightly, about 20 minutes more. Serve warm.

name: Copycat Kenny Rogers Chicken

steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Combine parsley, olive oil, red wine vinegar, garlic, red pepper flakes, oregano, and salt in a bowl. Set aside.. Remove the tough bottom leaves from each cauliflower, taking care not to remove the stem. Place the cauliflower heads onto a cutting board with the stem side facing upwards; cut vertically on both sides of the stem to remove the loose florets. Cut each cauliflower vertically through the stem into 2 even "steaks", 1 to 1 1/2 inches thick; remove any remaining small leaves from each steak. Reserve remaining cauliflower for another use.. Place cauliflower steaks on the baking sheet. Brush both sides with olive oil and sprinkle with garlic salt.. steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease a 9X13-inch baking dish.. Cook bacon in a skillet over medium heat, turning occasionally, until crisp, about 7 minutes. steps: Gather all ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Add cream of chicken soup, heavy whipping cream, cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, salt, garlic powder, and onion powder to a large saucepan over medium. Cook, stirring often, until cream cheese mixture is melted, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in thyme and pepper. Add potatoes and toss to coat fully.. Spoon half of the potato mixture into a 9x13-inch baking dish. Using the back of a large spoon, gently press down and spread potatoes in an even layer; sprinkle with 1 cup of the cheese. Top with remaining potato mixture, gently pressing down and spreading potatoes in an even layer. Set aside.. Stir together crackers, butter, and remaining 1 cup cheese in a small bowl until evenly coated; sprinkle over potatoes. Transfer baking dish to a large-rimmed baking sheet. Cover baking dish with aluminum foil.. Bake in preheated oven, until the sauce thickens and potatoes are tender, about 1 hour 40 minutes, removing aluminum foil after 1 hour 10 minutes.. steps: Combine parsley, cilantro, serrano peppers, garlic, 1/3 cup extra-virgin olive oil, lemon juice, and cumin in a blender. Pulse until smooth. Set aside.. ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'poblano peppers'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Mexican crema'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chicken bouillon granules'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Oaxaca cheese'}
steps: Place poblano chiles directly on the grates of a gas stove. Cook over medium heat, flipping with tongs occasionally, until blackened and charred, about 5 minutes. Place in a sealed plastic bag and allow to cool, 5 to 6 minutes. Peel off charred skins, remove seeds, and slice chiles into strips. Set aside.. Melt butter in a large skillet. Add onions and cook until soft and translucent, 6 to 7 minutes. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add poblano peppers, Mexican crema, salt, chicken bouillon, and pepper; cook and stir until combined. Turn off heat, add cheese, and stir until melted.

name: Spicy Pickled Cucumbers
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '7', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'peppercorns'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pickling spice'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'mustard seeds'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'fresh dill to taste'}
steps: Rinse cucumbers and pat dry. Trim off the ends, then slice in half. Slice each half into spears. Place spears in a clean, wide mouth mason-type canning jar.. Add water, vinegar, and honey to a saucepan. Add about half the garlic pieces, then drop the remaining garlic into the jar with cucumber spears.. Using a mortar and pestle, grind peppercorns, pickling spice, mustard seeds, and pepper flakes together. Sprinkle about half the mixture into the saucepan, then add remaining mixture to cucumber spears. Add as much fresh dill fronds as desired to the saucepan and also drop some into the pickle jar.. Add salt to the saucepan. Heat on low, stirring constantly, until the honey has melted. Pour over cucumber spears, filling jar to within 1/8-inch of rim, then close the lid on tightly. Refrigerate for 1 week before using.

name: Arroz Verde with Hatch Chiles
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green chiles'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'long grain rice'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'garlic cloves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chicken bouillon'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}
steps: Place Hatch chiles directly on the grates of a gas stove. Cook over medium heat, flipping with tongs occasionally, until blackened and charred, about 5 minutes. Place in a sealed plastic bag and allow to cool, 7 to 8 minutes.. Peel off charred skins; remove seeds. Place chiles, chicken broth and cilantro in the jar of a blender and blend until smooth. Set aside.. Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat until it shimmers; add rice and onion. Cook and stir until lightly browned, about 2 minutes. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Stir in chicken bouillon, salt, and cumin. Add chile mixture and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer until rice is tender, 25 to 30 minutes.

name: Chicken Spinach Alfredo Baked Stuffed Shells
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'jumbo pasta shells'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'rotisserie chicken'}, {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'ricotta cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh basil'}, {'quantity': '10', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'spinach'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg, beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '22 to 24', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'Alfredo sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded mozzarella cheese'}
steps: Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Add 4 1/2 teaspoons salt and pasta shells to water and boil, stirring occasionally, 9 minutes, Drain and set aside.. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Combine chicken, ricotta, basil, spinach, 3/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese, 1/2 teaspoon pepper, garlic powder and remaining salt in a large bowl and mix well. Stir in egg. Divide filling evenly among pasta shells.. Coat bottom of a 9x13-inch casserole dish with olive oil. Spread 1/2 cup Alfredo sauce along bottom of dish. Fill dish with stuffed shells and top with remaining sauce, shredded cheese and remaining Parmesan and  pepper. Cover with foil.. Bake in the preheated oven for 25 minutes. Uncover and bake until bubbly, 10 to 15 minutes more.. Turn the oven to broil on High. Broil until lightly browned on top, 3 to 4 minutes. Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

name: Grilled Salmon with Chimichurri
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'shallot'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'curly parsley'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'sprigs', 'name': 'fresh dill'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime, zested'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(3 ounce)', 'name': 'salmon filets'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'granulated garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: For chimichurri, add garlic and shallot to the bowl of a food processor and pulse 2 or 3 times. Add herbs, lime juice, and vinegar. Blend until finely chopped.. With the food processor still running, slowly drizzle in olive oil to emulsify. Add lime zest, salt, and pepper to taste and blend until smooth. Stir in red pepper flakes. Refrigerate until ready to use.. Prepare an outdoor grill for direct cooking over high heat, 450 to 550 degrees F (230 to 290 degrees C).. Generously coat the flesh side of the salmon fillets with oil and season evenly with granulated garlic, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper. Grill the salmon, skin side down, over direct high heat for 6 to 8 minutes.. Turn the salmon over, close the lid, and cook until fish flakes easily with a fork, 4 to 6 minutes longer. Transfer to a platter to rest for 1 to 2 minutes. Slide the salmon skin from the fillets and serve with chimichurri.

name: Lemony-Dill Bulgur Pilaf
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'bulgur'}, {'quantity': '2 to 3', 'unit': '2 to 3 cups', 'name': 'broth'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic,'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh dill'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon zest'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'tzatziki'}
steps: Heat oil in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Add bulgur (or other WHOLE GRAIN); cook, stirring occasionally, until toasted, about 4 minutes. Stir in vegetable broth ( or other BROTH), garlic, salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low. Simmer, covered, until grain is tender. (Timing will depend on grain. See “Cook Times.”). Remove from heat and let stand 10 minutes; drain any excess liquid. Stir in dill (or other HERB), lemon zest (or other ZEST), and lemon juice (or other JUICE). Spoon tzatziki (or other TOPPING) over servings.

name: Bang Bang Cauliflower
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'head', 'name': 'cauliflower'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'granulated garlic'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white pepper'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chili sauce'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'sriracha'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sesame seeds'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chives'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C) and line a 12x18-inch sheet pan with aluminum foil.. Toss cauliflower pieces with olive oil in a large bowl. Place cauliflower in a single layer on the prepared pan.. Whisk granulated garlic, smoked paprika, cayenne, salt, and white pepper together in a small bowl. Sprinkle mixture evenly over cauliflower pieces.. Bake in the center of the preheated oven until just barely tender, 10 to 15 minutes.. Make the sauce: stir mayonnaise, chili sauce, soy sauce, sesame oil, sriracha, and onion powder together in a small bowl. Drizzle about half of the sauce over the cauliflower pieces. Reserve remaining sauce for serving.. Stir the cauliflower and continue baking another 10 minutes, or until the cauliflower reaches the desired doneness.. Garnish with sesame seeds and fresh snipped chives. Serve with reserved sauce.

name: Air Fryer Sriracha Fries
ingredients: {'quantity': '2 to 3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'russet potatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'riracha'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Cut potatoes into fries. Place cut fries into a bowl of water; soak for 1 hour.. Preheat the oven to 200 degrees F (95 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with paper towels and set a wire rack over the sheet.. Preheat the air fryer to 375 degrees F according to manufacturer’s instructions.. Drain fries, and pat dry with a paper towel. Place fries in a resealable plastic bag. Add oil, 1 tablespoon Sriracha, and salt. Seal the bag and toss to coat.. Add fries to bottom of air fryer basket in a single flat layer, not stacked. You will have to work in batches.. Air fry until crispy and golden brown, about 13 minutes.. Place fries on the prepared baking sheet; keep warm in the preheated oven. Repeat with remaining fries.. Place fries on a platter; drizzle with remaining sriracha. Enjoy.

name: Mushroom Pilaf with Pine Nuts and Dried Cherries
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'cremini mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white rice'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'low-sodium vegetable stock'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pine nuts'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried cherries'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'fresh basil,'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Heat 2 teaspoons oil over medium heat in a large oven-safe skillet. Add mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned, about 8 minutes. Add remaining 1 teaspoon olive oil and the rice; cook, stirring occasionally, until rice is fragrant, about 2 minutes. Stir in stock, pine nuts, cherries, salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil.. Bake, covered, in the preheated oven until liquid is absorbed, about 17 minutes. Let stand, covered, 5 minutes. Fluff with a fork. Sprinkle with fresh basil.

name: Parmesan-Garlic Green Beans
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'green beans'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'minced garlic'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Arrange green beans on a parchment paper-lined rimmed baking sheet. Lightly coat with cooking spray. Sprinkle with black pepper; toss to coat.. Roast in the preheated oven until softened, 15 to 20 minutes.. Add Parmesan, garlic, and crushed red pepper; toss to coat. Roast until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle with additional cheese and crushed red pepper.

name: Squash Gratin with Mornay Sauce
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Vidalia onion'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'zucchini'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'yellow squash'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'fresh oregano'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'flour'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole milk'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Gruyere cheese'}
steps: Set oven rack 6 inches from heat source; preheat broiler. Bring water to a boil in a large skillet; add onion, zucchini, and yellow squash. Reduce heat; simmer, covered, until tender, 7 to 9 minutes. Drain. Transfer to a 1-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with oregano and 1/4 teaspoon salt.. In a small saucepan, heat oil over medium heat. Whisk in flour, pepper, and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt; cook until foaming, then whisk in milk until thickened, about 2 minutes. Stir in Gruyère cheese until melted; pour over vegetable mixture.. Broil until browned, about 2 minutes. Sprinkle with more oregano and pepper.

name: Honey Roasted Beets
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'beets'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Cut stems and leaves from beets and wash well. With skin on, cut beets into chunks. Toss beets in olive oil and sprinkle with salt. Spread beets in an even layer on the prepared baking sheet.. Roast in the preheated oven for 30 minutes.. Remove from the oven and drizzle with honey. Using a wooden spoon, stir beets to coat completely with honey, then spread them back out on the pan.. Continue roasting until tender, about 15 minutes. Allow to cool.

name: Crispy Air Fryer Potato Bites
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'red potatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}
steps: Preheat the air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) according to manufacturer’s instructions.. Place cubed potatoes in a large bowl. Add olive oil and toss to coat. Add garlic powder, salt and pepper; toss again. Add grated Parmesan and toss one last time.. Place seasoned potatoes in the basket of the preheated air fryer. Cook for 8 minutes. Shake and cook until tender, about 4 minutes more. Serve immediately.

name: Chicken Ricotta Meatballs
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'white onion'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ricotta cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground chicken'}, {'quantity': '15', 'unit': None, 'name': 'Roma tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, peeled'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'basil leaves, cut into thin strips, for garnish'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'shaved Parmesan, for garnish'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with foil or parchment paper.. Heat olive oil in a skillet. Add onion and garlic, season with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper, and cook until soft and translucent, 3 to 5 minutes. Let cool to room temperature.. Combine panko and ricotta in a bowl and mix well. Add egg and season with remaining salt, pepper and Italian seasoning; mix to combine. Add ground chicken, and cooked onion and garlic mixture; mix gently to combine.. Shape into about 24 meatballs and place on the prepared baking sheet.. Bake meatballs in the preheated oven until no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C),  about 20 minutes; remove to cool.. To make the sauce, preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).. Coat the tomatoes with olive oil, then place cut side down in a single layer on a rimmed baking sheet. Add onion and garlic cloves to the baking sheet and sprinkle everything with salt.. Roast in the preheated oven until tomato skins begin to shrivel and tomatoes begin to release their juice, about 25 minutes.. Remove and let cool slightly. Carefully discard the skins.. Place tomatoes, onion, and garlic in a blender and blend to your preferred consistency. Stir in Italian seasoning and serve with chicken meatballs. Garnish with basil and shaved Parmesan.

name: Sweet and Spicy Sweet Potato Bites

steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (225 degrees C). Stir onion powder, garlic granules, paprika, sugar, coriander, salt, oregano, and parsley together in a small bowl; set seasoning aside.. Add sweet potatoes to a large bowl or resealable plastic bag. Add the oil; sprinkle in about 1 tablespoon seasoning. Toss to coat potatoes. Extra seasoning can be stored in an airtight jar.. Bake in the preheated oven until tender, about 25 minutes.

name: Crispy Corn
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'oil for frying'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(15 ounce) cans', 'name': 'sweet corn,'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cornstarch'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime wedges'}
steps: Heat oil in a medium saucepan to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Pour drained corn on a large plate lined with paper towels and pat dry,. Toss corn with cornstarch until lightly coated. Work in batches, about 1/2 cup at a time. Shake off excess cornstarch and carefully lower corn into hot oil, using a slotted spoon. Fry until lightly golden brown and crispy, 2 to 3 minutes; drain on paper towels. Repeat with remaining corn.. Season with paprika and pepper; squeeze lime juice over and sprinkle with jalapenos if desired.

name: Spinach, Feta, and Rice Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'scallions'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'drained, chopped sun-dried tomatoes in oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) package', 'name': 'spinach'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'vegetable broth'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'white rice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh lemon juice (from 1 lemon)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'feta cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh dill'}
steps: Gather all ingredients. Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (190 degrees C).. Heat oil in a large ovenproof skillet over medium-high heat. Add scallions, sun-dried tomatoes, garlic, and oregano; cook, stirring often, until scallions soften, about 2 minutes. Add spinach, and cook, stirring occasionally, until thawed, 5 to 6 minutes.. Stir in broth, rice, lemon zest and juice, salt, pepper, and 1 cup of the feta. Bring to a simmer over high heat, stirring occasionally. Stir in dill, and top evenly with remaining 1/2 cup feta.. Bake in the preheated oven until rice is tender and feta begins to brown, about 20 minutes.
